<p>For centuries, it was here, at the Town Fountain, that people used to fill up on water, until piped water arrived. People can sit and rest on the bench there, while they enjoy the water that some believe to have healing power.</p>
<p>The monument dates back from the sixteenth century. It still preserves characteristic elements from that time – the shield and the royal crown on the top, below the cornice.</p>
<p>It is big enough to put the pitcher inside to draw water and exhibits a square shape with three spouts on figureheads. The book Aquilégio Medicinal, from 1726, the first inventory of Portuguese mineral waters, considers the water from this fountain tasty and diuretic.</p>
